{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "404d7841-a2b2-47ba-872a-e42ce68c1d64",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "machine learning:\n",
    "it is a branch of ai which learns from the past data to predict the future values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "bacf2a92-a04a-4d62-8bcf-94c81398e479",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "types of machine learning:\n",
    "1.supervised learning\n",
    "2.unsupervised learning\n",
    "3.reinforcement learning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9578ea29-b1c9-4c40-a88c-56d3cec3f7ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1.supervised learning:\n",
    "which learns from the labelled data(structured data)\n",
    "\n",
    "types of supervsied learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.regression\n",
    "2.classification\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "86197271-ecce-417b-a754-fc40216e17c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1.regression:\n",
    "it is used to show the relationship between two variables (independent/dependent)\n",
    "and the target/output/dependent variable should be continuous\n",
    "Algorithms in regression:\n",
    "\n",
    "Linear regression[simple,multi]\n",
    "polynomial regression\n",
    "logistic regression(cart)\n",
    "decision tree(cart)\n",
    "random forest(cart)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a4d7730d-54c0-407f-b667-0451b6be76a1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2.classification:\n",
    "The output variable should be categorical\n",
    "\n",
    "Algorithms in classification\n",
    "\n",
    "Logistic regression\n",
    "decision tree\n",
    "naive bayes\n",
    "k nearest neighbors\n",
    "random forest"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "39469f14-6ed0-4fb0-82bb-3c0889485b0a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2.unsupervised learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "it is mainly used to work on unlabelled data(unstructured data)\n",
    "\n",
    "types of unsupervised learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "2.Association rule learning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fe8d97cc-990f-4cbb-a16b-fcf81894316d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1.clustering:\n",
    "it is used to group the similar data elements\n",
    "\n",
    "Algorithms available in clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "Kmeans clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "hiearchical clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "dbscan(density based spatial clustering of applications with noise)\n",
    "\n",
    "gmm(gaussian mixture models)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9de9ab58-1d13-448c-a16f-dcf83c34094e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2.Association rule learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "it is used to identify the frequent patterns inside the data\n",
    "\n",
    "Algorithms available in association rule learning\n",
    "\n",
    "Apriori\n",
    "eclat\n",
    "fp growth"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9ee87cc0-7923-44c2-b9cd-6b54a8894e5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3.Reinforcement:\n",
    "\n",
    "it is a feedback learning\n",
    "\n",
    "for every right action you will get the reward\n",
    "\n",
    "for every wrong action you will get the penality"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6415d69a-d210-45b9-973d-e0228012d171",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Applications:\n",
    "\n",
    "Ecommerce:\n",
    "\n",
    "product recommendations\n",
    "\n",
    "health care:\n",
    "\n",
    "disease prediction\n",
    "patient risk analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "self driving cars\n",
    "\n",
    "object detection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "479a4ac1-c9c2-4d91-b8c6-c393ecd12e8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "life cycle of machine learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "business understanding\n",
    "\n",
    "data collection\n",
    "\n",
    "data preparation/data preprocessing/data cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "exploratory data analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "feature engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "model selection\n",
    "\n",
    "model training\n",
    "\n",
    "model evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "data deployement\n",
    "\n",
    "maintaining and monitoring"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "071578ff-c352-4a17-a922-e926f643d24a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Linear regression:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.simple linear regression\n",
    "\n",
    "2.multi linear regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f383f205-fc1e-4fc6-a9cc-52b5b9275dcd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "independent and dependent variables\n",
    "\n",
    "independent/input/features\n",
    "dependent/output/target"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "2a55a3f9-038b-4738-a86a-2c0487a47da6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "marketing_spend[independent]\n",
    "sales[dependent]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "0646ccd2-f002-44a7-85f0-02f65ff279e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "simple linear regression:\n",
    "\n",
    "if you have one independent variable and one dependent variables then it is called as simple linear\n",
    "regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9c06fc32-8c5b-4e39-bbd7-45380ac51115",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Multi linear regression:\n",
    "\n",
    "if you have more than one independent variable and one dependent variable then it is called as multi linear\n",
    "regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "79418ba8-6156-4303-a7ad-3400819cf7f7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "simple linear regression(mathematical):\n",
    "it shows the relationship between independent and dependent variable in a straight line\n",
    "\n",
    "y=mx+c\n",
    "\n",
    "where y is dependent variable\n",
    "m is slope\n",
    "x is independent variable\n",
    "c is intercept"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "39c455cb-74ae-40a5-8c6a-20a84a44f735",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "loss function: it shows the error rate between actual value and the predicted value then it is called\n",
    "as loss function/cost function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a7ffb4bd-d1c8-4fd6-8ff3-5e9cfea21a6f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "low loss function---high accuracy\n",
    "high loss function---low accuracy\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ef0c6ad5-36ca-4aa5-a7f7-74255e9ef8f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "hypothesis:assuming that our data will be having relationship between independent and dependent variable"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3671af61-5325-41c0-b26c-70956983ab8e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Evaluation metrics for the regression models:\n",
    "\n",
    "mean square error(mse)\n",
    "\n",
    "mean absolute error(mae)\n",
    "\n",
    "root mean square error(rmse)\n",
    "\n",
    "r2 score(accuracy)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "01987c94-641d-4bb2-99fc-a23778b42e6e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "optimization:improving the model performance by decreasing the loss function then it is called as\n",
    "optimization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8f26ef66-0210-4d55-830b-816c1866d92b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Assumptions of linear regression:\n",
    "1.linearity:\n",
    "the relationship between independent and dependent variables\n",
    "\n",
    "2.homoscedasiticty of residuals:\n",
    "the variance of residuals remains constant across all the levels of independent variables\n",
    "\n",
    "3.auto correlations:\n",
    "it shows the mislead conclusions\n",
    "\n",
    "4.lack of multi collinearity:\n",
    "\n",
    "the independent variables are not highly correlated with each other\n",
    "\n",
    "5.normality:\n",
    "\n",
    "the residuals are different for actual and the predicted values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3dc1e8aa-b81c-4b50-9e7c-f6a143607446",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Lasso regression(L1 regularization):\n",
    "it is a linear regression technique that adds a penality to the loss function to prevent the model\n",
    "from overfitting.this penality is based on absolute values of the coefficients"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c8b7b867-3728-44e6-81b5-4a7226dc0d4b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ridge regression(L2 regularization):\n",
    "it is a technique which is used to prevent the model from overfitting problems"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "4abd4d6d-7175-4c5b-9f00-730f54c17f4a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "elastic net(L1 & L2 regularization)\n",
    "combination of lasso and ridge is called as elastic net"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d2e364a6-2bc6-40d1-9553-d8c28481ed47",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "gradient descent:\n",
    "finds the optimal values of weights and biases by gradually reducing\n",
    "the error between predicted and actual outputs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "dd20eed9-2018-491a-88cf-48fc44ed5051",
